Lagos – Lagos State government has partnered with the Pro-Poor Growth and Promotion of Employment in Nigeria (SEDIN) programme of the German Development Agency (GIZ) to improve ease of doing business in the state. Markus Wauschkuhn, Head of Programme, GIZ-SEDIN, while speaking at a validation workshop of the Report on Barometer of the Investment Climate in Lagos State, said that programme is committed to improving the employment situation of Nigeria through the support of SMEs. He said GIZ-SEDIN is specifically working with its partners to address bottlenecks that are hindering businesses from scaling and creating more jobs. NYSC Trust Fund: DG Commends Nigerians, Reps As 1,700 Begin… Port Protests: Customs Delegation Visits Lagos, Examines Agents’… Vincent Nwani, a consultant who worked on the report while presenting key findings, said that 500 businesses in the state were engaged in the survey. He said the top 10 best performing indicators are airport standard, ICT standard, quality of healthcare system, leisure and culture, university system, measures to tackle investment obstacles, science, and technology, high-end talents, and registration.